{"analytics_identifier":"OT1266","base_path":"/government/organisations/single-financial-guidance-body","content_id":"ccc9dff8-87b7-4d0f-8d78-b8339063b440","description":"The Money and Pensions Service (MaPS) replaces the 3 existing providers of government-sponsored financial guidance – the Money Advice Service, the Pensions Advisory Service and Pension Wise. It provides free and impartial debt advice, money guidance and pension guidance to members of the public. The organisation was set up as the Single Financial Guidance Body (SFGB) on 1 October 2018. It was renamed the Money and Pensions Service (MaPS) in April 2019. MaPS is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Work and Pensions .","details":{"acronym":"MaPS","alternative_format_contact_email":"","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Money and Pensions Service (MaPS) replaces the 3 existing providers of government-sponsored financial guidance – the Money Advice Service, the Pensions Advisory Service and Pension Wise. It provides free and impartial debt advice, money guidance and pension guidance to members of the public.</p>\n\n<p>The organisation was set up as the Single Financial Guidance Body (SFGB) on 1 October 2018. It was renamed the Money and Pensions Service (MaPS) in April 2019.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Money and Pensions Service\">MaPS</abbr> is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions\">Department for Work and Pensions</a>.</p>\n</div>","brand":"department-for-work-pensions","foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"no-identity","formatted_title":"Money and Pensions Service"},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[],"ordered_featured_documents":[],"ordered_featured_links":[],"ordered_promotional_features":[],"organisation_featuring_priority":"news","organisation_govuk_status":{"status":"exempt","updated_at":null,"url":"https://moneyandpensionsservice.org.uk/"},"orga